Visitor Center
You head into a building that is made of decorative concrete that follows an unusual concave curve. You open the door to the Visitor Center that has faux dinosaur bones as the handle. In the middle of the room you see a beautiful T-Rex skeleton and against that, you see a sauropod Alamosaurus. There is a plastic welcome sign hanging above the dinosaurs. This looks like a really nice park. You are taken to the showcase theater. 

You take a seat and suddenly an animated film starts called Mr. DNA. It stars an old man named John Hammond and an animated DNA strain. The film talks about how DNA from extinct animals has been hiding around the world. Wow; they are really going all in with the dinosaur theme! It is talking about mosquitoes and how they would suck the blood of dinosaurs and then mosquitoes would get stuck in tree sap, eventually becoming amber. The video explains that scientists were able to extract the DNA from the mosquitoes and use the DNA of a frog to complete the DNA sequence to create dinosaurs. This video is getting really weird. The video further explains that this has allowed the park to make baby dinosaurs. Everyone in your test groups looks around in disbelief. 

Your seats are taken past the window of a lab...and what you see in the lab is astounding. There are dinosaur eggs everywhere and you see that little baby dinosaurs are hatching! They did it. They made dinosaurs come to life!  You can’t believe it. You are taken out to the center of the Visitor Center

