Head to the Park
It is time to head to the park. You get on a self-driving truck that is supposed to drive you around a track to see all the dinosaurs. The ground is lush green and everything looks beautiful. The first location you head to is the Proceratosaurus Field. 

You learned that this is more of a smaller dinosaur with a bump on its nose and that it is a meat eater. You wait in the car and hope one will come by the fence to give you a look. You are so excited and get your disposable camera ready to snap a photo. You see bushes moving and start to get nervous because even though it is a plant-eating dinosaur, they are pretty big. You see over the bush a nose bump. You can hear their noises and know that they travel as part of a pack. You learned that the park has made all the dinosaurs female so that they cannot reproduce. 

The  Gallimimus Exhibit is next. This breed of dinosaur is much smaller than the other; they mainly ate insects and very small prey. They move like birds and stay together. They are rather loud and make squeaking noise.

Next you head to the Brachiosaurus Enclosure. You see long fields of grassy plains. There is a lagoon and suddenly you see one of the giant Brachiosaurus getting a drink. It lifts its head and looks over the fence at you as the jeep moves, but you see even more Brachiosauruses in the enclosure. They are huge and they have a lot of room to move around. You snap a photo with your camera. 

Suddenly your jeep gets stuck on the track. You hear an announcement on the truck's  speakers saying to stay in the car and wait until they can restart the system. 

